1
00:00:19,227 --> 00:00:21,981
( crickets chirping )

2
00:00:21,981 --> 00:00:23,482
( dog barking )

3
00:00:30,489 --> 00:00:31,907
( stairs creaking )

4
00:00:34,033 --> 00:00:35,577
( door opening )

5
00:00:44,085 --> 00:00:46,005
I can see you.

6
00:00:48,382 --> 00:00:50,718
JAVIER: ...pull into
this gas station,
the guy was like,

7
00:00:50,718 --> 00:00:52,511
"Yo, man,
you got problems."

8
00:00:52,511 --> 00:00:55,054
Like, "What the hell
do you think
I pulled in here for?"

9
00:00:55,054 --> 00:00:59,393
So your car broke down
on the way to your blood check.

10
00:00:59,393 --> 00:01:02,354
Yeah, smoke,
everything.

11
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:05,148
I'm willing to give you the
benefit of the doubt, Javier,

12
00:01:05,148 --> 00:01:07,317
but a judge won't.

13
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:09,737
I missed a couple
of meetings?

14
00:01:09,737 --> 00:01:11,989
What's the problem?
I mean, I don't even know

15
00:01:11,989 --> 00:01:14,033
what I'm doing here.
You're here because your son

16
00:01:14,033 --> 00:01:15,910
has gotten into fights
every day at school,

17
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:18,787
and the last one sent
one of his classmates
to the hospital.

18
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:20,581
Juanita came here
for help voluntarily

19
00:01:20,581 --> 00:01:23,000
before the court stepped in
and made it mandatory,

20
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,711
that's what
you're doing here.

21
00:01:25,711 --> 00:01:27,922
He's on a
dangerous road.

22
00:01:27,922 --> 00:01:31,800
Your history, all the violence,
all the anger,

23
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:35,345
that's his future
unless you break the cycle.

24
00:01:35,345 --> 00:01:36,764
I heard you, Mrs. Lynch.

25
00:01:36,764 --> 00:01:38,766
( over phone ): You're
trying to steal my boy!

26
00:01:38,766 --> 00:01:40,434
No one is trying
to steal your child.

27
00:01:40,434 --> 00:01:42,310
Then what are you trying...
They found bruises

28
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:43,771
and cigarette burns...
I told you,

29
00:01:43,771 --> 00:01:45,773
he was playing
with some sparklers.

30
00:01:45,773 --> 00:01:47,608
Mrs. Lynch, I read
the medical report.

31
00:01:47,608 --> 00:01:49,610
I don't wanna talk about it
I want a lawyer.

32
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:51,403
If you feel that you need
legal representation

33
00:01:51,403 --> 00:01:53,530
that's perfectly
within your rights...

34
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:56,450
I don't need your help,
in no case. You've already
interfered enough.

35
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:57,743
You... Hello?

36
00:01:57,743 --> 00:01:59,118
( dial tone beeps )

37
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,831
How many active
cases you got?

38
00:02:02,831 --> 00:02:04,583
Thirty-eight.

39
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:06,251
Okay.

40
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:08,629
Wayne, come on!

41
00:02:08,629 --> 00:02:10,089
Look, I'm buried here.

42
00:02:10,089 --> 00:02:12,173
I'm sorry, Em,
we all are.

43
00:02:12,173 --> 00:02:14,175
(people chattering )

44
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:21,600
( sighing )

45
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,544
ANSWERING MACHINE: You have
three new voice messages.

46
00:04:12,544 --> 00:04:13,795
Hi.

47
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:15,714
( beeping )

48
00:04:15,714 --> 00:04:18,759
Hey, it's Suze, missed you
at yoga the other day,
give me a call.

49
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:22,387
Hey, Em, it's Jackie.
Just checking in,
hope you're good.

50
00:04:23,847 --> 00:04:27,142
DOUG: Exhausted,
her career path
questionable,

51
00:04:27,142 --> 00:04:29,728
her faith in
mankind shaken,

52
00:04:29,728 --> 00:04:31,772
she resisted her tendency
toward introspection

53
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:35,776
and decides to go
have a drink with her
charming friend Doug.

54
00:04:35,776 --> 00:04:36,985
(people chattering )

55
00:04:36,985 --> 00:04:39,529
I am so in your head.
Be honest.

56
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:42,616
The whole psychology
thing, it's just about
scoring chicks, isn't it?

57
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:44,868
Regrettably, yes.
Mmm-hmm.

58
00:04:44,868 --> 00:04:46,203
Two.

59
00:04:47,454 --> 00:04:49,497
Well, what are we
gonna drink to tonight?

60
00:04:49,497 --> 00:04:51,708
The never-ending
fun of a career
in public service?

61
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:53,627
Yeah.

62
00:04:53,627 --> 00:04:56,964
You know,
I sit there talking
to these families,

63
00:04:56,964 --> 00:04:59,007
the authority
on everything.

64
00:04:59,007 --> 00:05:03,845
And I have these moments
where I think I might
be totally full of it.

65
00:05:03,845 --> 00:05:06,098
Everybody's
full of it.

66
00:05:06,098 --> 00:05:07,682
In the end you're
a number to call

67
00:05:07,682 --> 00:05:10,185
for people who don't
have anyone else.

68
00:05:10,185 --> 00:05:12,395
There's no way
that's bad.

69
00:05:14,273 --> 00:05:20,028
Anyway, I've done
some soul searching

70
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:21,863
and I just want to say

71
00:05:21,863 --> 00:05:25,117
that if a full-on
relationship feels like
too much right now,

72
00:05:25,117 --> 00:05:28,620
I'd be willing to
consider a purely
physical one.

73
00:05:30,914 --> 00:05:33,541
What?
Nothing.

74
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:35,127
What, you might actually
enjoy yourself.

75
00:05:35,127 --> 00:05:37,045
Yeah, yeah,
I probably would.

76
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,255
( laughs )

77
00:05:38,255 --> 00:05:40,757
It's just...

78
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:43,384
I know, I know,
the job,

79
00:05:43,384 --> 00:05:46,638
you get home, no time
for anybody else. Whatever.

80
00:05:46,638 --> 00:05:49,183
Listen, I'm giving you a month.
Okay? One month.

81
00:05:49,183 --> 00:05:50,433
And then?

82
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:52,060
I don't know.

83
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:54,437
Probably give you
another month, but that is it.

84
00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:57,565
Except for two more,
then, it's over.

85
00:06:06,241 --> 00:06:08,451
If it were
anyone...

86
00:06:27,137 --> 00:06:29,348
What are they
doing to you?

87
00:06:53,621 --> 00:06:55,207
( dog barking )

88
00:06:55,207 --> 00:06:56,541
( children laughing )

89
00:07:26,238 --> 00:07:27,655
What?

90
00:07:27,655 --> 00:07:30,075
Emily Jenkins.
Child Services?

91
00:07:30,075 --> 00:07:31,826
We spoke
on the phone?

92
00:07:31,826 --> 00:07:33,578
You said the 17th.

93
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:34,996
It's the 17th.

94
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:36,206
Is not.

95
00:07:36,206 --> 00:07:38,125
I'm sorry,
but it is.

96
00:07:40,335 --> 00:07:43,964
Monday the 17th.
The day of our
appointment.

97
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:13,160
Hi.

98
00:08:14,995 --> 00:08:17,497
Come down,
I'd like to meet you.

99
00:08:32,095 --> 00:08:34,889
My name's Emily.
What's yours?

100
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,810
Lily.

101
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:40,519
That's a pretty name.

102
00:08:42,481 --> 00:08:45,108
Is there somewhere
we can talk?

103
00:08:46,818 --> 00:08:49,612
So, when are you
expecting your
husband back?

104
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:52,907
Because we've found
that it's better

105
00:08:52,907 --> 00:08:56,370
when the whole family
participates.

106
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:58,538
Well, he's not
here, so...

107
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,415
Do you have some way
of contacting him?

108
00:09:00,415 --> 00:09:03,001
Not if I don't
know where he is.

109
00:09:03,001 --> 00:09:04,543
( electric whirring )

110
00:09:04,543 --> 00:09:06,380
EMILY: Is that...

111
00:09:07,755 --> 00:09:10,717
Would you mind
asking him to
join us, please?

112
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:13,303
He doesn't have
anything to say.

113
00:09:13,303 --> 00:09:14,888
Will you ask
him, please?

114
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:23,313
MARGARET: Edward.

115
00:09:23,313 --> 00:09:25,773
That lady is here
from the state.
She wants to talk to you.

116
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:28,567
EDWARD: I don't have
anything to say,
tell her that!

117
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:30,987
I told her already,
she wants to anyway.

118
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:32,322
( clanging )

119
00:09:34,449 --> 00:09:36,076
( whispers ):
It'll be okay.

120
00:09:36,076 --> 00:09:37,452
( door opening )

121
00:09:41,622 --> 00:09:43,666
( inaudible )

122
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:49,464
Hi, I'm Emily.

123
00:09:52,759 --> 00:09:54,469
Okay.

124
00:09:54,469 --> 00:09:57,222
I'm here because
we received a call

125
00:09:57,222 --> 00:10:01,393
that Lilith
is showing serious
signs of neglect.

126
00:10:01,393 --> 00:10:03,228
Now at this point
we can only assume

127
00:10:03,228 --> 00:10:06,064
it's the result
of family problems.

128
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:11,945
( inaudible )

129
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:22,414
Eddie says
we don't have
family problems.

130
00:10:22,414 --> 00:10:25,292
Well, many families
won't realize that
they're having problems

131
00:10:25,292 --> 00:10:28,587
until it's too late.
And that's where
we come in.

132
00:10:28,587 --> 00:10:30,547
We help families
communicate

133
00:10:30,547 --> 00:10:33,883
and learn healthier ways
of resolving conflict.

134
00:10:41,224 --> 00:10:44,478
Eddie says we don't
need your help.

135
00:10:44,478 --> 00:10:46,521
Mr. Sullivan,
is there a reason

136
00:10:46,521 --> 00:10:48,815
why you won't speak
to me directly?

137
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:56,156
Is there a reason why
your husband won't
speak to me directly?

138
00:10:57,532 --> 00:10:59,284
( stamping foot )

139
00:11:03,288 --> 00:11:06,291
Eddie doesn't like
speaking out of anger.

140
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:25,352
There's no laws
against being
weird, Em.

141
00:11:25,352 --> 00:11:27,521
I didn't say weird,
I said scary.

142
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:30,231
That man sat there
staring at me
the whole time,

143
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:32,817
and the mother is
his emotional slave.

144
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:35,736
Wait, you didn't just fly
to New York and meet
with my parents, did you?

145
00:11:35,736 --> 00:11:37,614
Wayne?

146
00:11:37,614 --> 00:11:40,074
( sighs ): All right.
All right. Are there
any cuts, any bruises,

147
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:42,076
any signs she's
being abused?

148
00:11:42,076 --> 00:11:45,664
No, not physically.
But this girl's in
trouble, I can feel it.

149
00:11:45,664 --> 00:11:46,998
You wanna know
what I can feel?

150
00:11:46,998 --> 00:11:48,458
The lawsuit we're
gonna get hit with

151
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:50,126
if we violate
her parents' rights

152
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:52,212
without any evidence
they've done
something wrong.

153
00:11:52,212 --> 00:11:54,839
All right, Wayne.
You put these
files on my desk

154
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:56,633
and you ask me
to tell you
what's going on.

155
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:58,717
I've told you,
I've done my job,

156
00:11:58,717 --> 00:12:00,887
what you do
with it is yours.

157
00:12:00,887 --> 00:12:02,180
( stutters )

158
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:24,285
We're not
perfect parents,
we know that,

159
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:26,246
but we figure
if they know how
much you love them

160
00:12:26,246 --> 00:12:29,416
a lot of the other stuff
takes care of itself.

161
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:36,673
She knows how
we feel about her.

162
00:12:37,674 --> 00:12:39,926
So, tell me,
Mr. Sullivan,

163
00:12:39,926 --> 00:12:42,470
since you've suddenly
acquired the
ability to speak,

164
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:44,681
doesn't it concern
you a little

165
00:12:44,681 --> 00:12:48,476
that Lily's grades have
dropped from A's to D's
in three months?

166
00:12:48,476 --> 00:12:50,937
Of course it does,
she's our daughter.

167
00:12:50,937 --> 00:12:54,815
So you have no idea why
your daughter falls asleep
in class every day?

168
00:12:54,815 --> 00:12:57,694
Why she can't sleep
at home? No idea?

169
00:13:00,697 --> 00:13:03,283
Bad dreams maybe?

170
00:13:05,452 --> 00:13:08,246
Don't tell me you're buying
this whole "daddy's
little girl" routine?

171
00:13:08,246 --> 00:13:10,290
Look, they're not
my favorite people
either, okay?

172
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:12,584
But we can't
guarantee every kid
a happy childhood.

173
00:13:12,584 --> 00:13:14,001
I wish we could.

174
00:13:14,001 --> 00:13:16,254
Let me talk to her.
She wants to talk.
Alone.

175
00:13:16,254 --> 00:13:18,005
Em, we do not
have a case.

176
00:13:18,005 --> 00:13:19,924
Just five minutes, okay?

177
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:22,927
Talk to them about
how much they love kids.

178
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:31,561
( children laughing )

179
00:13:31,561 --> 00:13:33,772
Hey, girls,
slow down!

180
00:13:35,649 --> 00:13:38,859
I used to wish
I had a sister when
I was growing up.

181
00:13:38,859 --> 00:13:40,570
To play with
and to talk to

182
00:13:40,570 --> 00:13:42,614
about all those
things that you
just can't tell

183
00:13:42,614 --> 00:13:44,491
anybody else,
you know?

184
00:13:44,491 --> 00:13:47,744
Did you ever wish that?
That you had a sister?

185
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:55,209
( gasps )

186
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:57,295
( giggling )

187
00:13:57,295 --> 00:13:59,589
( grunts )

188
00:13:59,589 --> 00:14:02,883
Well, that was
a silly thing to do,
wasn't it?

189
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:07,430
What's happening
with you?

190
00:14:13,478 --> 00:14:17,064
You know I can help.
Let me help you.

191
00:14:18,775 --> 00:14:20,943
What is it,
sweetheart?

192
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:27,241
They hate me.

193
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:30,161
I'm sure they
don't hate you.

194
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:32,955
They do.
I hear them.

195
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:40,630
They go into the
cellar and talk.

196
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:42,841
What do they
talk about?

197
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:49,096
Sending me
to hell.

198
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:53,267
You heard
them say that?

199
00:14:54,769 --> 00:14:56,312
( recorder clicks )

200
00:14:59,190 --> 00:15:03,319
You can tell him.
He's on your side.
It's okay.

201
00:15:06,656 --> 00:15:10,660
Lily, did you hear
your parents say they
were gonna hurt you?

202
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:33,767
( elevator dings )

203
00:15:57,206 --> 00:16:01,711
I was just thinking
about you, got a nice letter
from Sandy Hutchinson.

204
00:16:05,131 --> 00:16:07,133
Well, well, well.

205
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:09,803
It's sitting right in
front of me, which means
our good friend Wayne

206
00:16:09,803 --> 00:16:12,764
has decided it fails
to meet the criteria
for child endangerment

207
00:16:12,764 --> 00:16:15,475
and has told you in
no uncertain terms
to leave it alone.

208
00:16:15,475 --> 00:16:18,728
Surprise, surprise.
I'm sorry, Emily. I can't.

209
00:16:18,728 --> 00:16:21,856
Please, Mike,
I'm really
desperate here.

210
00:16:23,942 --> 00:16:25,359
( typing )

211
00:16:29,697 --> 00:16:31,031
Emily.

212
00:16:32,909 --> 00:16:35,995
Now, you know how
dear to my heart
the work you do is,

213
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:39,916
but the department doesn't
pay me to stake out
potential child abusers.

214
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:42,084
Last time almost
cost me my job.

215
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:44,921
This little girl heard
her parents say

216
00:16:44,921 --> 00:16:47,590
they're going to
send her to hell.

217
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:50,134
Sickening as that is,

218
00:16:50,134 --> 00:16:53,596
you're a part of the
system that deals with
those situations, I'm not.

219
00:16:53,596 --> 00:16:55,974
Mmm-hmm. But sometimes
the system doesn't work.

220
00:16:55,974 --> 00:16:58,309
Well, maybe you
should just let it.

221
00:16:58,309 --> 00:17:02,104
Wow. Feel like
I'm talking
to Wayne here.

222
00:17:02,104 --> 00:17:04,774
All right. You don't
want to get involved,
that's fine,

223
00:17:04,774 --> 00:17:08,068
but don't bullshit me,
Mike, I'm running out
of people I respect.

224
00:17:08,068 --> 00:17:10,028
Okay. No bullshit.
Bring me evidence

225
00:17:10,028 --> 00:17:12,866
of a crime,
I'm all over it.
Till then...

226
00:17:20,498 --> 00:17:21,916
( Edward panting )

227
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:33,135
( school bell ringing )

228
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:34,637
( children chattering )

229
00:17:43,813 --> 00:17:46,024
BOY: Let's go,
hurry up!

230
00:17:46,024 --> 00:17:48,234
Lily! Lily!

231
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:52,822
( Emily exclaims )

232
00:17:52,822 --> 00:17:57,869
Hi. I came to
tell you I hadn't
forgotten about you.

233
00:17:58,995 --> 00:18:00,914
I'm doing
everything I can.

234
00:18:03,374 --> 00:18:07,169
If I disappear
will you come
look for me?

235
00:18:08,421 --> 00:18:11,049
You're not
going to disappear.

236
00:18:11,049 --> 00:18:12,341
If I do?

237
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,177
( school bus honking )

238
00:18:15,177 --> 00:18:19,515
I have to go.
They get mad at me
when I miss the bus.

239
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:24,395
Lily, wait. Wait.

240
00:18:27,982 --> 00:18:30,568
Here. It's my
home number.

241
00:18:32,737 --> 00:18:36,532
If you get scared,
I want you to
call me, okay?

242
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:40,661
I'm gonna get you out
of there, I promise.

243
00:18:42,413 --> 00:18:43,706
Okay.

244
00:18:56,134 --> 00:18:57,511
( phone ringing )

245
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:03,935
Hey, this is Doug,
here it comes.

246
00:19:03,935 --> 00:19:05,561
( beeping )

