Omelet's getting cold.
Better hurry.

503
00:40:29,844 --> 00:40:31,554
( people chattering )

504
00:40:31,554 --> 00:40:35,558
You watch, six months,
their lawyer
will hire an expert

505
00:40:35,558 --> 00:40:39,187
to say they're rehabbed
and they'll sue for
custody when they get out.

506
00:40:39,187 --> 00:40:41,231
She's not going
back there.

507
00:40:41,231 --> 00:40:44,109
I'll take her out
of the state before I
let them near her again.

508
00:40:44,109 --> 00:40:46,319
Didn't hear
you say that.

509
00:40:47,946 --> 00:40:50,282
You guys okay?

510
00:40:50,282 --> 00:40:51,408
Mmm-hmm.

511
00:40:51,408 --> 00:40:54,035
We're great.
She's sweet,

512
00:40:54,035 --> 00:40:56,037
very intuitive
about everything.

513
00:41:00,417 --> 00:41:03,336
You wanted to talk
about something?

514
00:41:03,336 --> 00:41:05,504
We pulled the Ramirezes'
phone records.

515
00:41:05,504 --> 00:41:08,091
There was a call
that night
before the murder.

516
00:41:08,091 --> 00:41:09,342
From who?

517
00:41:09,342 --> 00:41:12,137
The call came from
your house, Emily.

518
00:41:12,137 --> 00:41:13,512
What?

519
00:41:13,512 --> 00:41:14,931
I'm not accusing
you of anything,

520
00:41:14,931 --> 00:41:16,266
I just want to
know what was said.

521
00:41:16,266 --> 00:41:18,393
But that's impossible.

522
00:41:18,393 --> 00:41:20,979
I mean, I might have called
them the week before
or something, but I...

523
00:41:20,979 --> 00:41:24,149
I'm talking to you
as a friend, you
know that, right?

524
00:41:24,149 --> 00:41:26,192
Mike, did you
not hear me?

525
00:41:26,192 --> 00:41:30,238
As a friend, I'm telling
you that I didn't
call that family.

526
00:41:34,826 --> 00:41:36,244
He's in my group.

527
00:41:37,787 --> 00:41:40,957
Why, did
something happen?

528
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:45,795
We're trying to
figure out why.

529
00:41:45,795 --> 00:41:48,798
Diego got a call
from here, last
Thursday night.

530
00:41:48,798 --> 00:41:51,092
I'm just wondering
if he might
have said something.

531
00:41:51,092 --> 00:41:52,635
That wasn't me.

532
00:41:52,635 --> 00:41:54,012
You didn't call him?

533
00:41:55,638 --> 00:41:59,142
Lily, it's difficult
sometimes to tell
the truth,

534
00:41:59,142 --> 00:42:01,644
but I know you will
because you're
a good kid.

535
00:42:01,644 --> 00:42:04,147
I am telling the truth.

536
00:42:04,147 --> 00:42:08,276
My backup files
are in the cabinet.
Diego's is in there.

537
00:42:08,276 --> 00:42:13,198
Maybe you got curious
and went through some,
dialed a number?

538
00:42:13,198 --> 00:42:16,451
It wasn't me,
I swear.

539
00:42:16,451 --> 00:42:20,372
The call came at 2:00 a.m.
You ever up that late?

540
00:42:20,372 --> 00:42:21,747
I didn't call him.

541
00:42:21,747 --> 00:42:23,291
You ever up that late?

542
00:42:23,291 --> 00:42:26,503
Mike, she said no.
Maybe somebody
made a mistake.

543
00:42:27,837 --> 00:42:29,422
Yeah, maybe so.

544
00:42:36,137 --> 00:42:40,308
Why would Diego do this?
He loved his mom and dad.

545
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:43,061
You never want to
think anyone you know

546
00:42:43,061 --> 00:42:45,313
is capable of
that kind of thing.

547
00:42:45,313 --> 00:42:49,317
In your mind, it's always
some nameless,
faceless creature.

548
00:42:50,902 --> 00:42:54,322
Sometimes, the city
seems full of them.

549
00:42:54,322 --> 00:42:57,409
But they're just people,
like you and me.

550
00:43:00,161 --> 00:43:01,662
She's lying.

551
00:43:05,958 --> 00:43:07,877
( gasps )

552
00:43:07,877 --> 00:43:09,962
Do you believe me?

553
00:43:11,214 --> 00:43:12,798
I believe you.

554
00:43:16,844 --> 00:43:20,806
I need to ask you
something about the
night it happened.

555
00:43:20,806 --> 00:43:23,976
Did you get a call?
Really late?

556
00:43:27,397 --> 00:43:28,940
You didn't.

557
00:43:30,567 --> 00:43:32,860
Diego, I know
that you did.

558
00:43:34,779 --> 00:43:37,115
The call came
from my house.

559
00:43:39,825 --> 00:43:41,411
( gasping )

560
00:43:41,411 --> 00:43:42,745
What's the matter?

561
00:43:42,745 --> 00:43:44,080
( choking )

562
00:43:44,080 --> 00:43:46,749
What's scaring you?
Diego.

563
00:43:48,167 --> 00:43:50,336
It's okay,
it's all right.
Deep breaths,

564
00:43:50,336 --> 00:43:51,712
deep breaths,
you'll be all right.

565
00:43:51,712 --> 00:43:54,507
Can we get some
help in here, please?

566
00:43:58,719 --> 00:44:00,430
( beeping, door closing )

567
00:44:08,104 --> 00:44:11,816
Who called you?
Was it Lily?

568
00:44:14,902 --> 00:44:16,904
Did she say
something to you?

569
00:44:16,904 --> 00:44:18,864
Something
that scared you?

570
00:44:20,325 --> 00:44:23,702
El dijo.
"El dijo"?

571
00:44:24,829 --> 00:44:27,706
What do you mean,
"He said"?

572
00:44:27,706 --> 00:44:30,876
Era un hombre.

573
00:44:30,876 --> 00:44:32,337
It was a man?

574
00:45:00,865 --> 00:45:02,783
( chair squeaking )

575
00:45:09,999 --> 00:45:13,252
Do you

576
00:45:13,252 --> 00:45:17,089
like working here?

577
00:45:18,257 --> 00:45:20,843
Well, photocopying
isn't much fun.

578
00:45:23,054 --> 00:45:24,847
What?
Knock, knock.

579
00:45:24,847 --> 00:45:26,349
Sorry I'm late, guys.

580
00:45:26,349 --> 00:45:28,393
You ready to go, kiddo?

581
00:45:28,393 --> 00:45:31,270
So, how's school?

582
00:45:31,270 --> 00:45:33,231
Fine.

583
00:45:33,231 --> 00:45:35,316
Any of your classmates
giving you a hard time?

584
00:45:35,316 --> 00:45:37,943
No, they've been nice.

585
00:45:39,571 --> 00:45:41,780
You sleeping okay?

586
00:45:41,780 --> 00:45:45,868
That's not really what
you want to talk about,
is it, Doug?

587
00:45:45,868 --> 00:45:47,328
You got me.

588
00:45:50,415 --> 00:45:54,085
Question 16, am I
afraid of the dark?
You answered no.

589
00:45:54,085 --> 00:45:59,507
Question 23, am I
afraid of being alone?
You answered no.

590
00:45:59,507 --> 00:46:01,926
26, am I afraid
of my parents? No.

591
00:46:01,926 --> 00:46:05,762
You answered no
to everything
in that section.

592
00:46:05,762 --> 00:46:08,765
I think that some of those
should have been yeses.

593
00:46:08,765 --> 00:46:10,393
Everybody is
scared of something.

594
00:46:10,393 --> 00:46:12,437
Working through our fears,
conquering them,

595
00:46:12,437 --> 00:46:14,272
is how we get better.

596
00:46:15,607 --> 00:46:18,984
So, I want you
to tell me,
what scares you?

597
00:46:21,446 --> 00:46:26,825
I'll tell you what
scares me if you tell
me what scares you.

598
00:46:29,704 --> 00:46:31,330
( laughs ):
Fair enough.

599
00:46:34,166 --> 00:46:36,168
When I was a kid,
I was climbing a tree,

600
00:46:36,168 --> 00:46:39,046
and I accidentally put
my hand through a giant
hornets' nest.

601
00:46:39,046 --> 00:46:42,341
And they didn't
like it. I was stung
over a hundred times.

602
00:46:42,341 --> 00:46:45,720
They had to rush
me to the hospital.

603
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:48,347
Been afraid of
hornets ever since.

604
00:46:49,474 --> 00:46:52,560
I don't climb
many trees either.

605
00:46:52,560 --> 00:46:56,188
Everybody has fears.
Now, what scares you?

606
00:46:56,188 --> 00:46:58,149
Me.

607
00:46:58,149 --> 00:46:59,900
You scare yourself?

608
00:46:59,900 --> 00:47:01,152
Sometimes.

609
00:47:01,152 --> 00:47:04,238
Why? What about
yourself scares you?

610
00:47:06,115 --> 00:47:08,159
I have bad thoughts.

611
00:47:08,159 --> 00:47:09,786
About what?

612
00:47:09,786 --> 00:47:11,120
People.

613
00:47:11,120 --> 00:47:14,332
People in general
or certain people?

614
00:47:14,332 --> 00:47:15,750
Certain people.

615
00:47:15,750 --> 00:47:17,752
Like who?
You.

616
00:47:19,587 --> 00:47:22,047
You have bad
thoughts about me?

617
00:47:23,132 --> 00:47:24,425
Why?

618
00:47:24,425 --> 00:47:25,802
( scoffing ): I just do.

619
00:47:27,762 --> 00:47:31,432
Did I do something
or say something
that upset you?

620
00:47:31,432 --> 00:47:35,311
It's just the
way you are.

621
00:47:36,521 --> 00:47:37,896
How am I?

622
00:47:39,732 --> 00:47:41,484
Facile.

623
00:47:41,484 --> 00:47:43,402
Facile?

624
00:47:43,402 --> 00:47:44,570
( laughs )

625
00:47:44,570 --> 00:47:46,447
Do you even know
what that means?

626
00:47:46,447 --> 00:47:51,160
Easily comprehended.
Often lacking
sincerity or depth.

627
00:47:51,160 --> 00:47:52,911
You're smug, too.

628
00:47:54,205 --> 00:47:57,208
Want me to tell
you what that means?

629
00:47:57,208 --> 00:47:59,918
If I seemed smug
or facile I want to...

630
00:47:59,918 --> 00:48:01,838
( laughs ):
Don't apologize.

631
00:48:01,838 --> 00:48:03,631
Why not?

632
00:48:03,631 --> 00:48:08,093
You're a grown-up.
It's embarrassing.

633
00:48:17,311 --> 00:48:22,441
Number 12, I worry
about what's going
to happen.

634
00:48:22,441 --> 00:48:23,984
Yes or no?

635
00:48:23,984 --> 00:48:26,362
You want me
to answer that?

636
00:48:26,362 --> 00:48:28,364
Yes or no?

637
00:48:28,364 --> 00:48:29,824
No.

638
00:48:31,576 --> 00:48:33,452
That should be a yes.

639
00:48:37,914 --> 00:48:40,752
Should we talk
about school now?

640
00:48:40,752 --> 00:48:43,421
My grades are
getting a lot better.

641
00:48:49,926 --> 00:48:54,766
I talked to a lot of kids,
I don't think I've ever
felt like that before.

642
00:48:54,766 --> 00:48:56,141
Like what?

643
00:48:57,142 --> 00:48:59,061
( sighs ): Threatened.

644
00:48:59,061 --> 00:49:00,438
( elevator dings )

645
00:49:05,150 --> 00:49:08,863
I know a specialist,
I'm gonna call
him in the morning.

646
00:49:14,911 --> 00:49:16,287
( chair squeaking )

647
00:49:51,447 --> 00:49:52,949
Are you mad at me?

648
00:49:52,949 --> 00:49:56,577
No. No,
I'm just tired.

649
00:49:56,577 --> 00:49:59,246
Want me to
brush your hair?

650
00:49:59,246 --> 00:50:01,332
No, thanks.

651
00:50:01,332 --> 00:50:03,167
Are you sure?

652
00:50:03,167 --> 00:50:04,836
Some other time.

653
00:50:04,836 --> 00:50:08,255
It will make you
feel better.
I'll get the brush.

654
00:50:08,255 --> 00:50:10,215
I said no,
thank you.

655
00:50:17,431 --> 00:50:19,934
Doug said something,
didn't he?

656
00:50:22,144 --> 00:50:27,065
Doug? No. Doug says
you're doing great.

657
00:50:27,984 --> 00:50:29,986
What did he tell you?

658
00:50:29,986 --> 00:50:31,320
Nothing.

659
00:50:51,507 --> 00:50:53,425
( phone ringing )

660
00:51:03,602 --> 00:51:04,854
Hello.

661
00:51:04,854 --> 00:51:06,397
( static over phone )

662
00:51:14,906 --> 00:51:16,824
Try again, sorry.

663
00:51:38,387 --> 00:51:40,514
