688
00:55:50,722 --> 00:55:53,391
PRIEST: For as much
as it hath pleased
Almighty God,

689
00:55:53,391 --> 00:55:56,728
of his great mercy,
to take unto
himself the soul

690
00:55:56,728 --> 00:55:58,689
of our dear brother,
here departed,

691
00:55:58,689 --> 00:56:02,400
we, therefore,
commit his body
to the ground.

692
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:07,239
Earth to earth,
ashes to ashes
and dust to dust,

693
00:56:09,325 --> 00:56:12,911
in sure and certain
hope of the resurrection
to eternal life,

694
00:56:12,911 --> 00:56:15,998
through our Lord,
Jesus Christ, amen.

695
00:56:25,049 --> 00:56:26,591
( Emily crying )

696
00:56:48,155 --> 00:56:51,950
You think it's my
fault, don't you?

697
00:57:01,210 --> 00:57:05,339
It's no one's fault.
It was an accident.

698
00:57:20,020 --> 00:57:21,521
BARRON: There was
no sign of forced entry,

699
00:57:21,521 --> 00:57:23,732
he was alone
and the doors
were locked.

700
00:57:23,732 --> 00:57:27,403
I know he didn't
kill himself.
He was scared.

701
00:57:27,403 --> 00:57:30,948
He came out of that
room with her, Mike,
and he was scared.

702
00:57:30,948 --> 00:57:32,657
He said she
threatened him.

703
00:57:32,657 --> 00:57:35,035
Emily, you're in shock,
let's not get carried away.

704
00:57:35,035 --> 00:57:38,705
Diego, he said it was
a man on the phone.

705
00:57:38,705 --> 00:57:40,374
There was no one
else in the house.

706
00:57:40,374 --> 00:57:42,667
Do you think I don't know
how crazy this sounds?

707
00:57:42,667 --> 00:57:45,461
Kid in that state of mind
is not the most
reliable witness.

708
00:57:45,461 --> 00:57:49,049
But why was he in
that state of mind?
Why was Doug?

709
00:57:51,093 --> 00:57:53,678
Pull my phone records.
See if she called him.

710
00:57:53,678 --> 00:57:56,556
I already did, Emily.
There was no call.

711
00:57:58,142 --> 00:58:01,353
So, you're saying that
you've seen this before,

712
00:58:01,353 --> 00:58:04,898
someone just
dying like that?

713
00:58:04,898 --> 00:58:06,775
Truly?

714
00:58:06,775 --> 00:58:10,279
I'm shocked
every day by the violence
people do to themselves.

715
00:58:10,279 --> 00:58:15,993
Her mom and dad had
deadbolts on their
bedroom door, big ones.

716
00:58:17,577 --> 00:58:21,373
Something came
through that door,
and whatever it was,

717
00:58:21,373 --> 00:58:24,876
they didn't want it
ever coming through
there again.

718
00:58:28,255 --> 00:58:30,048
Hey guys, come on,
are you ready?

719
00:58:30,048 --> 00:58:31,716
Yeah.

720
00:58:31,716 --> 00:58:33,885
WOMAN: Let's get to it?
MAN: Yeah.

721
00:58:48,025 --> 00:58:49,485
( elevator bell dings )

722
00:59:00,954 --> 00:59:05,501
MALE INTERVIEWER: Take me
through the conversation,
Margaret, about the oven.

723
00:59:05,501 --> 00:59:08,420
Eddie said,
"We're gonna burn her,"
and I said, "Okay."

724
00:59:08,420 --> 00:59:10,339
So it was
Edward's idea?

725
00:59:10,339 --> 00:59:12,883
Just the oven part,
we both wanted her dead.

726
00:59:12,883 --> 00:59:16,512
Why did you say that it
was God's will that you
should kill your daughter?

727
00:59:16,512 --> 00:59:17,762
( chuckles )

728
00:59:17,762 --> 00:59:18,972
Why is that funny,
Margaret?

729
00:59:18,972 --> 00:59:20,598
'Cause she's
not my daughter.

730
00:59:20,598 --> 00:59:23,185
You think your
daughter is the devil?

731
00:59:23,185 --> 00:59:24,769
Evil incarnate?

732
00:59:24,769 --> 00:59:26,688
I don't care
what you call it.

733
00:59:26,688 --> 00:59:29,358
But you have stated
that she kills people?

734
00:59:29,358 --> 00:59:33,778
Not by her own hand,
they just die.

735
00:59:33,778 --> 00:59:35,613
I had two brothers,

736
00:59:37,574 --> 00:59:40,327
Eddie had
three sisters.

737
00:59:40,327 --> 00:59:44,706
( crying): Soon as
she was born, they
just started dying.

738
00:59:48,502 --> 00:59:50,379
Me and Eddie, I guess,

739
00:59:52,339 --> 00:59:56,260
she couldn't get rid
of us until she found
somebody else.

740
01:00:11,191 --> 01:00:13,527
MAN: The nurse on duty
heard screaming,

741
01:00:13,527 --> 01:00:17,322
found Mrs. Sullivan
on the floor clawing
at her own skin,

742
01:00:17,322 --> 01:00:20,158
absolutely convinced
she was on fire.

743
01:00:24,996 --> 01:00:27,165
( Margaret gasping )

744
01:00:29,084 --> 01:00:30,586
( crying )

745
01:00:30,586 --> 01:00:33,922
In no condition
for visitors
as you can see.

746
01:00:33,922 --> 01:00:38,051
If you'd like,
I can let you
see Mr. Sullivan.

747
01:00:38,051 --> 01:00:39,344
Okay.

748
01:00:42,931 --> 01:00:44,266
( gasps )

749
01:01:00,824 --> 01:01:04,953
I know I'm probably
the last person you
want to see right now,

750
01:01:04,953 --> 01:01:10,000
but you're the only
one that I can talk to.

751
01:01:10,000 --> 01:01:11,376
Who died?

752
01:01:13,670 --> 01:01:16,548
A friend.
You're scared.

753
01:01:17,799 --> 01:01:19,551
You ought to be.

754
01:01:21,803 --> 01:01:23,847
Is she...

755
01:01:26,724 --> 01:01:30,604
What is she?
I can tell you
what she's not.

756
01:01:30,604 --> 01:01:33,982
She's not a daughter of mine.
She's not a 10-year-old
having trouble in school.

757
01:01:33,982 --> 01:01:36,901
And she's not some
innocent victim whose
door you busted down

758
01:01:36,901 --> 01:01:38,987
and life you saved.

759
01:01:38,987 --> 01:01:42,115
She's not going
anywhere soon, lady.

760
01:01:42,115 --> 01:01:44,242
Not till she's good
and done with you.

761
01:01:44,242 --> 01:01:47,412
Done with me how?
However she wants.

762
01:01:48,913 --> 01:01:51,500
You think it's an accident
her ending up with you?

763
01:01:51,500 --> 01:01:54,211
She saw you
coming a mile away.

764
01:01:54,211 --> 01:01:58,340
Why me? I don't
have anything.

765
01:01:58,340 --> 01:02:00,509
You have that
you're good.

766
01:02:00,509 --> 01:02:03,428
Kindness. Decency.
That's what
she feeds on.

767
01:02:03,428 --> 01:02:07,558
Bleeds you dry,
moves on to the next.

768
01:02:07,558 --> 01:02:09,893
We were a big family,

769
01:02:09,893 --> 01:02:12,563
she went through us
like a wrecking ball.

770
01:02:12,563 --> 01:02:16,650
It's like she
sees everything.

771
01:02:16,650 --> 01:02:21,279
And what she
doesn't see,
she senses.

772
01:02:21,279 --> 01:02:25,825
Like when you call
a friend and they pick
it up before it rings?

773
01:02:25,825 --> 01:02:28,119
( chuckles ):
They say
when you're born

774
01:02:28,119 --> 01:02:30,830
you're given
your eternal soul.

775
01:02:30,830 --> 01:02:34,418
The part of you that
lives on, lives again.

776
01:02:34,418 --> 01:02:39,256
Whatever evil she is,
didn't come from us.

777
01:02:39,256 --> 01:02:41,174
It was already there.

778
01:02:41,174 --> 01:02:44,720
From the moment she
came into being, she brought
something with her.

779
01:02:44,720 --> 01:02:47,222
Something older,
destructive.

780
01:02:49,057 --> 01:02:50,808
Soul of a demon.

781
01:02:56,607 --> 01:02:58,816
What does she want?

782
01:02:58,816 --> 01:03:03,029
To know what your
idea of hell is

783
01:03:05,449 --> 01:03:07,200
and make you
live there.

784
01:03:53,204 --> 01:03:54,539
( lock clicking )

785
01:03:56,750 --> 01:03:58,042
( school bus stopping )

786
01:04:43,129 --> 01:04:44,631
( door opening )

787
01:04:52,681 --> 01:04:54,599
Hi.
Hi.

788
01:04:55,891 --> 01:05:00,146
You weren't there
so I took the bus.

789
01:05:00,146 --> 01:05:03,066
Sorry, work,
I lost track of time.

790
01:05:04,900 --> 01:05:07,654
It's okay,
I know how busy you are.

791
01:05:09,740 --> 01:05:15,036
Doesn't matter anyway,
the bus stops right at
the end of the street.

792
01:05:15,036 --> 01:05:20,041
So I can always get home,
whether you're there or not.

793
01:05:20,041 --> 01:05:21,376
Lucky.

794
01:05:25,171 --> 01:05:26,964
Where's the phone?

795
01:05:27,883 --> 01:05:30,093
It wasn't working, so...

796
01:05:37,893 --> 01:05:41,563
Wow. That one, too.

797
01:05:45,483 --> 01:05:49,613
We had gym today.
I'm gonna have a shower.

798
01:05:53,867 --> 01:05:55,869
Are they being
nice to her?

799
01:05:55,869 --> 01:05:57,120
Who?

800
01:05:57,120 --> 01:05:58,538
My mother.

801
01:06:00,457 --> 01:06:02,626
How would I know that?

802
01:06:02,626 --> 01:06:05,796
I thought you said
you were going to see her.

803
01:06:08,590 --> 01:06:10,759
I never said that.

804
01:06:10,759 --> 01:06:12,176
Hmm.

805
01:06:14,262 --> 01:06:16,222
I must have dreamt it.

806
01:06:33,406 --> 01:06:35,325
EMILY: Nancy.

807
01:06:35,325 --> 01:06:37,410
Emily.

808
01:06:37,410 --> 01:06:41,623
I'm so sorry about Doug.
I know you two were close.

809
01:06:41,623 --> 01:06:44,083
Do you have a minute?

810
01:06:44,083 --> 01:06:47,044
I was just wondering
if you've had any luck

811
01:06:47,044 --> 01:06:49,130
finding a place for Lilith?

812
01:06:49,130 --> 01:06:52,634
Still looking.
You know, more kids
than homes right now.

813
01:06:52,634 --> 01:06:54,928
So, how long
you think we're
talking here? Like...

814
01:06:54,928 --> 01:06:58,306
Honestly,
she's not my
first priority.

815
01:06:58,306 --> 01:07:01,142
She's in a safe environment
with someone who
understands her needs.

816
01:07:01,142 --> 01:07:02,560
Nancy,

817
01:07:04,103 --> 01:07:08,733
if there's anything that
you could do to expedite

818
01:07:08,733 --> 01:07:10,276
the process...

819
01:07:10,276 --> 01:07:12,111
Are you serious?

820
01:07:12,111 --> 01:07:15,824
Emily, you petitioned
for custody, you got it.

821
01:07:15,824 --> 01:07:18,535
She's your
responsibility.
Make it work.

822
01:07:18,535 --> 01:07:23,498
How?
How do I make it work
if it's not working?

823
01:07:23,498 --> 01:07:27,878
With the same coping
skills you teach these
moms and dads every week!

824
01:07:27,878 --> 01:07:31,631
Walk the talk, Emily!
Walk the talk!

825
01:07:31,631 --> 01:07:33,967
( therapist speaking
indistinctly )

826
01:07:39,180 --> 01:07:42,308
See you next time.
Good work.

827
01:07:42,308 --> 01:07:44,101
( children chattering )

828
01:07:54,696 --> 01:07:56,031
( inaudible )

829
01:08:13,381 --> 01:08:15,508
GIRL: Why is she hurting...

830
01:08:15,508 --> 01:08:19,512
Hey, wait a minute.
Who do you think you are,
barging in there like that?

831
01:08:19,512 --> 01:08:23,182
It's okay, Diane,
Emily's been under
a lot of stress lately,

832
01:08:23,182 --> 01:08:28,688
but she's really nice
to me and I hope I can
stay with her a long time.

833
01:08:28,688 --> 01:08:30,815
Don't ever do that again.

834
01:08:32,525 --> 01:08:34,360
LILITH: See you
next week, Diane.

835
01:08:34,360 --> 01:08:36,780
Don't worry,
it was all a
misunderstanding.

836
01:08:42,911 --> 01:08:45,455
You're not
going back there.

837
01:08:45,455 --> 01:08:47,665
Why, Emily?

838
01:08:50,460 --> 01:08:55,632
Why, Emily?
Why, Emily? Why, Emily?
Why, Emily? Why, Emily?

839
01:08:55,632 --> 01:09:00,887
Why, Emily?
Why, Emily? Why, Emily?
Why, Emily? Why, Emily?

840
01:09:00,887 --> 01:09:05,642
Why, Emily?
Why, Emily? Why, Emily?
Why, Emily? Why, Emily?

841
01:09:05,642 --> 01:09:09,479
( shouting ): Why, Emily?
Why, Emily? Why, Emily?
Why, Emily? Why, Emily?

842
01:09:09,479 --> 01:09:11,272
( elevator stopping )
Why, Emily?

843
01:09:14,818 --> 01:09:17,821
Can I go back to
group next week?

844
01:09:20,490 --> 01:09:23,076
You're never
going back there!

845
01:09:24,828 --> 01:09:27,162
Are you sure?

846
01:09:27,162 --> 01:09:28,832
( elevator cables creaking )

847
01:09:31,334 --> 01:09:34,211
No. No.

848
01:09:35,630 --> 01:09:37,590
( screams )

849
01:09:37,590 --> 01:09:39,425
( alarm beeping )

850
01:09:41,761 --> 01:09:43,096
( screaming )

851
01:09:49,435 --> 01:09:51,104
( elevator bell dinging )

852
01:10:17,212 --> 01:10:20,050
WOMAN 1: I know.
WOMAN 2: You were
terrific back there.

853
01:10:20,050 --> 01:10:22,510
MAN: Really enjoyed
the service, Father.
PRIEST: Thanks.

854
01:10:22,510 --> 01:10:24,345
Mike.

855
01:10:25,680 --> 01:10:27,473
Emily.

856
01:10:28,766 --> 01:10:32,854
They are not crazy,
Mike. Her parents.

857
01:10:32,854 --> 01:10:34,605
They're right about her.

858
01:10:34,605 --> 01:10:37,984
You want to wind up
where they are?
Keep talking like this.

859
01:10:37,984 --> 01:10:40,444
Emily, you're
grieving for Doug

860
01:10:40,444 --> 01:10:43,364
and you're still
confused about
what Diego did.

861
01:10:43,364 --> 01:10:46,201
Aren't you?
Diego grew up
in a bad home,

862
01:10:46,201 --> 01:10:48,995
he saw violence,
he repeated it,
that's the cycle.

863
01:10:48,995 --> 01:10:50,329
You know that
better than anyone.

864
01:10:50,329 --> 01:10:52,665
Why did she lie
about calling him?

865
01:10:52,665 --> 01:10:55,334
Because she's a liar,
but that doesn't mean
she made him do it.

866
01:10:55,334 --> 01:10:57,587
Let me tell you
what Lily is.

867
01:10:57,587 --> 01:11:02,717
She's a damaged child,
she's a deceitful child,
she's a manipulative child.

868
01:11:02,717 --> 01:11:06,387
But a damaged,
deceitful, manipulative
child is not a demon.

869
01:11:06,387 --> 01:11:08,347
You think I'm crazy.

870
01:11:10,141 --> 01:11:15,063
You believe in there.
But out here it's
all just bullshit?

871
01:11:15,063 --> 01:11:18,233
Mike, you know
I'm not crazy.

872
01:11:18,233 --> 01:11:21,611
Don't run away from this
just because it scares you.

873
01:11:21,611 --> 01:11:24,197
I'll tell you what is
scaring me is not
recognizing my friend.

874
01:11:24,197 --> 01:11:26,116
Get some help. Seriously.
Mike...

875
01:11:26,116 --> 01:11:28,492
I don't want to
report you.

876
01:11:34,207 --> 01:11:36,834
( clock ticking )

877
01:12:17,250 --> 01:12:18,751
Good night.

878
01:13:11,179 --> 01:13:12,596
( dialing )

879
01:13:17,143 --> 01:13:18,895
( phone ringing )

880
01:13:18,895 --> 01:13:21,231
Mrs. Lynch,
I told you that...

881
01:13:21,231 --> 01:13:24,108
( over phone ): Do you think
I'm an idiot? Do you think
I'm just making this up?

882
01:13:24,108 --> 01:13:26,319
That's not what you said.
I'm not stupid.
Yeah, no.

883
01:13:26,319 --> 01:13:28,321
You never said anything
about unsupervised visits.

884
01:13:28,321 --> 01:13:30,156
No, that is not
what I said.

885
01:13:30,156 --> 01:13:32,533
You said if my husband
got help, then my son
could come home.

886
01:13:32,533 --> 01:13:34,493
I did not. No.
Nothing between
the lines there.

887
01:13:34,493 --> 01:13:36,162
You never said that...
Who do you think you are

888
01:13:36,162 --> 01:13:38,039
telling me
how to raise my son?
Mrs. Lynch...

889
01:13:38,039 --> 01:13:40,208
You know nothing about me.
You know nothing about my son.

890
01:13:40,208 --> 01:13:41,709
Will you please
let me respond?

891
01:13:41,709 --> 01:13:43,418
How I raise my child is
none of your business.

892
01:13:43,418 --> 01:13:45,004
Would you let...
Would you...

893
01:13:45,004 --> 01:13:46,881
How my son and
his father relate...

894
01:13:46,881 --> 01:13:49,717
( shouting ): Shut the
fuck up, you miserable,
miserable woman

895
01:13:49,717 --> 01:13:52,595
before I come and
beat your ass like
you beat your son!

896
01:13:52,595 --> 01:13:54,430
I have your address!

897
01:13:54,430 --> 01:13:58,559
Think about that
before you call
and swear at me!

898
01:13:58,559 --> 01:14:02,563
Okay, so, you're certainly
in no state of mind to
be here right now.

899
01:14:02,563 --> 01:14:06,401
Come on, it's late,
you look like shit,
go home.

900
01:14:06,401 --> 01:14:08,903
I don't want to go home.

901
01:14:08,903 --> 01:14:10,571
( cell phone ringing )

902
01:14:14,909 --> 01:14:16,744
Hello?

903
01:14:16,744 --> 01:14:18,204
( static over phone )

904
01:14:26,045 --> 01:14:27,630
It's for you.

905
01:14:35,221 --> 01:14:36,847
Emily Jenkins.

906
01:14:36,847 --> 01:14:39,683
LILITH: You shouldn't
leave me home alone,
Emily.

907
01:14:47,650 --> 01:14:48,985
Wayne?

908
01:14:57,534 --> 01:14:59,870
( chair squeaking )

909
01:15:17,763 --> 01:15:19,432
( breathing heavily )

910
01:15:25,646 --> 01:15:26,981
( exhaling )

911
01:15:41,412 --> 01:15:43,747
There you are.
I made supper.

912
01:15:45,708 --> 01:15:49,670
Don't ignore me.
My mother used to
ignore me.

913
01:15:49,670 --> 01:15:51,130
( bolting door )

914
01:15:56,969 --> 01:15:58,429
( thunder rumbling )

915
01:16:17,365 --> 01:16:21,118
( knocking on door )
Emily? Can I come in?

916
01:16:22,412 --> 01:16:23,787
I'm scared.

917
01:16:23,787 --> 01:16:25,206
( knocking continues )

918
01:16:29,168 --> 01:16:31,546
( thuder clapping )

919
01:16:31,546 --> 01:16:37,510
Emily? Please?
I know you're in there.

920
01:16:38,844 --> 01:16:40,471
( banging door )
Please, Emily?

921
01:16:46,685 --> 01:16:48,062
( foosteps retreating )

922
01:17:03,578 --> 01:17:05,580
( banging, gasping )

923
01:17:07,790 --> 01:17:13,379
LILITH ( shrieking ):
Let me in, let me in.

924
01:17:13,379 --> 01:17:15,839
Let me in, let me in,
let me in, let me in,

925
01:17:15,839 --> 01:17:18,175
let me in,
let me in, let me in.

926
01:17:18,175 --> 01:17:20,010
( screaming ):
Leave me alone.

927
01:17:29,853 --> 01:17:31,314
( rattling )

928
01:18:10,561 --> 01:18:12,021
( screeching )

929
01:18:12,021 --> 01:18:13,606
( Emily screaming )

930
01:18:24,367 --> 01:18:25,701
( yelps )

931
01:18:39,465 --> 01:18:42,134
Please, help me.

932
01:18:43,760 --> 01:18:46,972
( banging on door )
Please! No, please
open the door?

933
01:18:46,972 --> 01:18:49,642
( screaming ):
Open the door,
she's coming!

934
01:18:51,018 --> 01:18:52,311
Drive.

935
01:18:52,311 --> 01:18:53,770
There's nobody out there.

936
01:18:55,189 --> 01:18:57,191
Drive!

937
01:18:57,191 --> 01:19:01,737
There is nobody
out there. Look.

938
01:19:07,284 --> 01:19:09,453
There's
nobody out there.

939
01:19:15,209 --> 01:19:16,669
( engine starting )

940
01:19:17,670 --> 01:19:19,255
( door opening )

941
01:19:36,230 --> 01:19:37,648
( panting )

942
01:20:00,045 --> 01:20:02,172
( softly ): It's okay.

943
01:20:02,172 --> 01:20:05,968
( screams ):
Leaving the child unattended
is a jailable offense.

944
01:20:09,805 --> 01:20:12,182
You have to do
what I say.

945
01:20:12,182 --> 01:20:16,811
If I say I want
to go to group,
you have to do it.

946
01:20:16,811 --> 01:20:22,526
If I say I want
a new dress,
you have to do it.

947
01:20:22,526 --> 01:20:27,030
If I say I want
ice cream every day,
after school,

948
01:20:28,282 --> 01:20:31,994
( crying ):
you have to do it,
okay?

949
01:20:35,372 --> 01:20:40,628
Don't be sad.
This is your
new beginning.

950
01:21:07,404 --> 01:21:08,739
Emily.

951
01:21:14,495 --> 01:21:19,583
I tried to call you.
Good news, we found
a home for Lily.

952
01:21:19,583 --> 01:21:22,712
Family in Cloverfield.
Really good people.

953
01:21:22,712 --> 01:21:25,881
They're picking
her up Friday,
after school.

954
01:21:27,717 --> 01:21:30,344
What's the matter?
They're perfect.

955
01:21:34,598 --> 01:21:36,016
EMILY: If they take her...

956
01:21:36,016 --> 01:21:38,602
The whole thing
starts all over again.

957
01:21:38,602 --> 01:21:41,230
You can't let her go,
you can't let her stay.

958
01:21:42,398 --> 01:21:45,067
Leaves you one option.
I can't.

959
01:21:45,067 --> 01:21:46,485
You have to.
You don't understand.

960
01:21:46,485 --> 01:21:47,820
Don't tell me I
don't understand.

961
01:21:47,820 --> 01:21:49,196
You've had her,
what, two months?

962
01:21:49,196 --> 01:21:51,490
I had her 10 years.
We had her 10 years.

963
01:21:51,490 --> 01:21:52,908
Think of it as
a test of faith.

964
01:21:52,908 --> 01:21:54,284
I don't wanna
have any faith.

965
01:21:54,284 --> 01:21:57,037
How about anger?
You got some of that?

966
01:22:06,547 --> 01:22:10,175
How? How do I...

967
01:22:10,175 --> 01:22:11,844
Kill her?

968
01:22:12,845 --> 01:22:14,889
In her sleep.

969
01:22:14,889 --> 01:22:16,557
That's the only time
you got the upper hand,

970
01:22:16,557 --> 01:22:18,893
is when she's sleeping,
but she almost never does.

971
01:22:18,893 --> 01:22:21,228
We checked on her room,
every night
for three months.

972
01:22:21,228 --> 01:22:25,232
First night she slept
was the night that you
busted in our front door.

973
01:22:25,232 --> 01:22:27,568
And I'll tell you
what I'd do different,

974
01:22:27,568 --> 01:22:29,737
count yourself
dead at the outset.

975
01:22:29,737 --> 01:22:33,240
Accept that going in,
use it to your advantage.

976
01:22:34,658 --> 01:22:37,620
If you're not afraid,
she can't hurt you.

977
01:22:41,998 --> 01:22:43,584
( sighs )

978
01:22:50,006 --> 01:22:51,592
( sighs )

979
01:23:01,852 --> 01:23:05,314
EDWARD ON TV: No money,
no way to contact her.

980
01:23:05,314 --> 01:23:08,901
Must have went 80
on the way back,
straight through,

981
01:23:08,901 --> 01:23:11,612
didn't stop for nothing.

982
01:23:11,612 --> 01:23:15,825
When we got home,
she was waiting for
us on the doorstep.

983
01:23:15,825 --> 01:23:20,329
Where is she now?
Some family, somewhere?

984
01:23:20,329 --> 01:23:23,874
MARGARET ON TV: Eddie said,
"We're gonna burn her,"
and I said, "Okay."

985
01:23:25,709 --> 01:23:29,296
They did what I
said for a while,
but then they stopped

986
01:23:30,380 --> 01:23:33,342
and started
with the secrets.

987
01:23:33,342 --> 01:23:36,679
But they weren't
really secrets,
I guess,

988
01:23:36,679 --> 01:23:39,807
because I always knew
what they were thinking.

989
01:23:47,857 --> 01:23:49,566
Don't leave me.

990
01:23:49,566 --> 01:23:52,152
It's okay, Maggie.
I'll check on you later.

991
01:23:57,741 --> 01:23:59,242
( door clicking )

992
01:24:03,079 --> 01:24:05,081
( Lilith screaming )

993
01:24:08,919 --> 01:24:10,504
( gasping )

994
01:24:11,588 --> 01:24:13,173
( crying )

995
01:24:14,216 --> 01:24:15,718
( screaming )

996
01:24:22,892 --> 01:24:24,434
( screaming )

997
01:24:30,440 --> 01:24:31,901
( men chattering )

998
01:25:00,971 --> 01:25:04,433
( in Lilith's voice ):
I'm glad you're getting
the help you need, Daddy.

999
01:25:06,142 --> 01:25:07,561
( screams )

1000
01:25:12,942 --> 01:25:14,317
( screaming )

1001
01:25:14,317 --> 01:25:15,652
( grunting )

1002
01:25:25,913 --> 01:25:27,372
MAN: Get somebody
down here now.

1003
01:25:27,372 --> 01:25:29,332
Somebody call it in.
Base, this is Sanchez.

1004
01:25:29,332 --> 01:25:32,544
We're gonna need
medical personnel right
away to the cafeteria...

1005
01:25:44,974 --> 01:25:47,141
Edward Sullivan...
I know.

1006
01:25:48,184 --> 01:25:50,520
Something
I want you to hear.

1007
01:25:50,520 --> 01:25:54,733
This came in this morning,
right about 2:00 a.m.

1008
01:25:54,733 --> 01:25:56,610
You might wanna sit.

1009
01:25:57,987 --> 01:26:00,280
( beeps )

1010
01:26:00,280 --> 01:26:03,617
LILITH: ( in deep voice ):
...decide what to do with
you and your family, Michael.

1011
01:26:03,617 --> 01:26:05,577
( static buzzing )

1012
01:26:05,577 --> 01:26:10,874
Every time I think
about it, a voice in my
head says, "Kill them."

1013
01:26:11,792 --> 01:26:13,919
DOUG: Who is this?

1014
01:26:13,919 --> 01:26:15,879
LILITH: ( in deep voice )
Just a little girl.

1015
01:26:17,380 --> 01:26:19,842
Up past her bedtime.

1016
01:26:19,842 --> 01:26:21,217
Lilith?

1017
01:26:21,217 --> 01:26:22,552
( Lilith giggling )

1018
01:26:25,973 --> 01:26:30,185
You were right.
She did call Doug.
She used your cell phone.

1019
01:26:31,979 --> 01:26:34,439
Took me a couple of
extra days to check
your cell phone records,

1020
01:26:34,439 --> 01:26:36,817
but that's what
she's been using.

1021
01:26:38,318 --> 01:26:39,778
She's tearing
me apart.

1022
01:26:39,778 --> 01:26:42,072
You're not crazy,
Emily. This is real.

1023
01:26:42,072 --> 01:26:44,491
Edward said
I have to kill her.

1024
01:26:51,874 --> 01:26:53,583
I'll help you.

1025
01:26:59,255 --> 01:27:01,257
Keep her at the house.

1026
01:27:01,257 --> 01:27:03,886
DOCTOR:
Physically you're fine.
How's the stress?

1027
01:27:03,886 --> 01:27:05,971
I'm not sleeping.

1028
01:27:05,971 --> 01:27:08,974
I was hoping
you could give
me something.

1029
01:27:10,600 --> 01:27:13,103
Take one of these,
you'll sleep.

1030
01:27:29,494 --> 01:27:30,829
Lily?

1031
01:27:57,647 --> 01:27:59,900
( dog growling )

1032
01:28:26,885 --> 01:28:29,012
What?

1033
01:28:31,514 --> 01:28:33,267
Oh, my God.

1034
01:28:37,562 --> 01:28:38,939
( growling continues )

1035
01:28:40,607 --> 01:28:42,234
( growling )

1036
01:28:49,365 --> 01:28:50,784
( loud buzzing )

1037
01:28:56,290 --> 01:28:57,582
( gun cocking )

1038
01:29:10,929 --> 01:29:12,472
( growling )

1039
01:29:17,060 --> 01:29:18,937
( gunshot )

1040
01:29:21,355 --> 01:29:23,525
( loud buzzing )

1041
01:29:35,287 --> 01:29:36,663
( cell phone buzzing )

1042
01:29:42,294 --> 01:29:43,628
( static over phone )

1043
01:29:48,091 --> 01:29:49,718
Who is this?

1044
01:29:49,718 --> 01:29:52,428
Emily, it's Wayne,

1045
01:29:52,428 --> 01:29:55,307
I just got a call,
Mike's dead.

1046
01:29:55,307 --> 01:29:57,433
No, he's...
Listen, Em.

1047
01:29:57,433 --> 01:30:00,270
They think
he shot himself.

1048
01:30:00,270 --> 01:30:02,731
Emily? Em?

1049
01:30:02,731 --> 01:30:04,607
( crying ): No...

1050
01:30:07,236 --> 01:30:11,907
Emily?
Emily, are you okay?

1051
01:30:11,907 --> 01:30:13,950
( hip-hop song playing on TV )

1052
01:30:22,209 --> 01:30:23,585
( crashing )

1053
01:30:25,212 --> 01:30:30,675
Get out of my house!

1054
01:30:39,851 --> 01:30:41,895
Get out of my house!

1055
01:30:49,611 --> 01:30:52,864
( in deep voice ):
Don't yell at me!

1056
01:30:57,369 --> 01:30:59,121
( panting )

1057
01:31:20,267 --> 01:31:24,646
LILITH: Emily,
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to.

1058
01:31:24,646 --> 01:31:28,024
Can I come in
so we can talk
and work it out?

1059
01:31:32,988 --> 01:31:34,530
Emily?

1060
01:31:35,698 --> 01:31:37,617
Stay away from me!

1061
01:31:37,617 --> 01:31:42,456
Don't be mad. I said
I was sorry. I'll brush
your hair for you.

1062
01:31:42,456 --> 01:31:44,207
Stay away from me!

1063
01:31:44,207 --> 01:31:45,541
( banging )

1064
01:32:03,268 --> 01:32:08,398
( screaming ):
No! No. No.

1065
01:32:18,908 --> 01:32:20,243
( gasps )

1066
01:32:25,957 --> 01:32:27,501
( screams )

1067
01:32:34,674 --> 01:32:39,888
LILITH: ( in deep voice ):
Emily. Emily.

1068
01:32:39,888 --> 01:32:44,184
We need to learn
healthier ways of
resolving conflict, Emily.

1069
01:32:47,937 --> 01:32:51,900
Most families
don't even know
they have a problem

1070
01:32:54,236 --> 01:32:55,987
until it's too late.

1071
01:33:04,079 --> 01:33:05,621
( grunts in male voice )

1072
01:33:09,625 --> 01:33:11,044
( chuckling )

1073
01:33:11,044 --> 01:33:14,214
What are you doing,
you silly pumpkinhead?

1074
01:33:14,214 --> 01:33:16,049
( chuckling nervously )

1075
01:33:16,049 --> 01:33:18,676
You don't want me
to come under there
and get you, do you?

1076
01:33:18,676 --> 01:33:19,928
( crying ): No.

1077
01:33:19,928 --> 01:33:21,595
I'm going to count to three.

1078
01:33:22,889 --> 01:33:26,684
One, two...

1079
01:33:26,684 --> 01:33:27,977
No.

1080
01:33:27,977 --> 01:33:31,356
Two and a half,
two and three quarters,

1081
01:33:32,941 --> 01:33:36,445
three. Here I come.

1082
01:33:37,695 --> 01:33:39,697
No! What do you want?

1083
01:33:39,697 --> 01:33:41,824
What you wanted
from your mother.

1084
01:33:44,494 --> 01:33:47,080
I want you to love me.

1085
01:33:49,749 --> 01:33:52,335
Okay. I will.

1086
01:33:55,964 --> 01:33:57,715
Come tuck me in.

1087
01:34:02,095 --> 01:34:04,013
( crying ): Oh, my God.

1088
01:34:05,557 --> 01:34:06,933
( kettle whistling )

1089
01:34:11,354 --> 01:34:12,772
LILITH: Emily.

1090
01:34:57,942 --> 01:34:59,528
Chamomile.

1091
01:35:04,698 --> 01:35:08,537
Maybe you should have it,
you look stressed.

1092
01:35:10,038 --> 01:35:11,914
I'll have one later.

1093
01:35:17,003 --> 01:35:20,714
I'm really sorry
that I let things
get like this.

1094
01:35:20,714 --> 01:35:22,676
We'll do better
from now on.

1095
01:35:22,676 --> 01:35:24,219
We have to.

1096
01:35:25,345 --> 01:35:27,681
Someone could get hurt.

1097
01:35:29,807 --> 01:35:32,101
What should
we do tomorrow?

1098
01:35:33,562 --> 01:35:35,564
Surprise me.

1099
01:35:35,564 --> 01:35:38,149
I'm not so good
at surprises.

1100
01:35:38,149 --> 01:35:40,485
You're getting better.

1101
01:37:19,751 --> 01:37:21,085
( glass shattering )

1102
01:37:39,853 --> 01:37:41,897
( sirens wailing )

1103
01:37:59,248 --> 01:38:01,083
( distorted ):
Everybody get out okay?

1104
01:38:03,211 --> 01:38:04,838
( Lilith chuckling )

1105
01:38:06,172 --> 01:38:09,175
Ma'am, anyone
else inside?
Yes or no?

1106
01:38:17,517 --> 01:38:19,101
That was mean.

1107
01:38:32,156 --> 01:38:37,078
You follow us downtown,
we'll find someplace
for you to stay.

1108
01:38:37,078 --> 01:38:39,247
Miss?
You okay?

1109
01:38:43,959 --> 01:38:45,503
I'm fine.

1110
01:38:52,301 --> 01:38:55,638
Maybe we can
find a hotel with
a swimming pool.

1111
01:38:59,975 --> 01:39:01,394
( tires screeching )

1112
01:39:06,775 --> 01:39:08,735
Where are we going?

1113
01:39:08,735 --> 01:39:11,320
You said
I should surprise you.

1114
01:39:16,910 --> 01:39:18,994
She hated herself.

1115
01:39:20,496 --> 01:39:22,373
And she hated you.

1116
01:39:22,373 --> 01:39:26,669
They said it was
an accident, but
you knew it wasn't.

1117
01:39:26,669 --> 01:39:28,379
Your mother.

1118
01:39:28,379 --> 01:39:30,715
That's why
you never had any
kids of your own.

1119
01:39:30,715 --> 01:39:33,384
That's what you're
afraid of, isn't it?

1120
01:39:33,384 --> 01:39:36,679
The part of you
that's her.

1121
01:39:37,971 --> 01:39:39,682
What are you?

1122
01:39:48,065 --> 01:39:50,735
Slow down!
What the hell are you?

1123
01:39:50,735 --> 01:39:54,906
You're upset,
you shouldn't
be driving.

1124
01:40:04,081 --> 01:40:07,168
( horns honking )

1125
01:40:11,589 --> 01:40:13,174
YOUNG EMILY: Mom.

1126
01:40:19,430 --> 01:40:21,641
( gasping )
Mom, slow down.

1127
01:40:21,641 --> 01:40:23,476
You're scaring me.

1128
01:40:30,232 --> 01:40:32,777
Mom!
Slow down, please!

1129
01:40:37,198 --> 01:40:38,783
Look out!

1130
01:40:41,118 --> 01:40:43,538
It's not real.
Yes, it is!

1131
01:40:45,581 --> 01:40:48,417
It's not real!

1132
01:40:55,341 --> 01:40:57,635
( laughing )

1133
01:41:01,639 --> 01:41:03,016
( panting )

1134
01:41:10,356 --> 01:41:11,983
Are you scared?

1135
01:41:17,655 --> 01:41:19,741
I'm not.

1136
01:41:19,741 --> 01:41:21,034
( gasps )

1137
01:41:36,799 --> 01:41:38,133
( grunts )

1138
01:41:49,979 --> 01:41:51,313
( gasps )

1139
01:41:54,483 --> 01:41:56,151
( distorted ):
I'm not afraid.

1140
01:42:05,828 --> 01:42:08,205
( screaming )

1141
01:42:09,164 --> 01:42:11,751
( Lilith screaming )

1142
01:42:13,795 --> 01:42:15,671
Just die!

1143
01:42:55,711 --> 01:43:00,133
( screaming ): No! No!

1144
01:43:02,927 --> 01:43:04,929
No!

1145
01:43:31,330 --> 01:43:32,665
( gasping )

1146
01:44:12,788 --> 01:44:14,123
( panting )

1147
01:44:31,974 --> 01:44:34,476
( sirens wailing )

1148
01:45:35,121 --> 01:45:38,207
( "Army of Angels" playing )

